        "Document Management System",
        "The Project Company shall establish and maintain an electronic Document Management System to store, catalogue and maintain all Project Records during the Term.",
        "The system shall be electronically searchable and legible and the Independent Engineer and GOU shall be provided with download access to it. The Project Company shall train the Independent Engineer and GOU in the operation of the system that shall be accessible online.",
        "The Project Company shall:",
        "Prepare a naming convention for all files/ project records;",
        "Provide for the secure access of data and transfer of data to the Independent Engineer or GOU when required;",
        "Provide for secure document and data storage with access controls to ensure that documents and data are protected from loss, theft, damage, unauthorised access or malicious use;",
        "Provide integration with Project scheduling software;",
        "Provide for upload, electronic storage and electronic transfer of data in native format as may be required from the Independent Engineer or GOU along with the associated searchable portable document format (PDF) images; and,",
        "Provide the Independent Engineer and GOU with procedures for accessing the Document Management System.",
        "Prior to implementing the Document Management System, the Project Company shall submit to the Independent Engineer for review and approval.",
        "The Project Company shall provide for backup/ disaster recovery of all documentation in the event that the data storage is compromised.",
        "Handback Requirements",
        "General",
        "This Section sets forth the minimum requirements for Handback at the end of the Term, including Handback Tasks, Handback Evaluation Criteria, test procedures, standards and reporting.",
        "The Project Company shall rehabilitate any asset that has reached the end of its design life, cannot be maintained to perform within the service level requirements, exhibits a measurably higher failure rate, or ceases to be economical to maintain due to excessive deterioration or obsolescence.",
        "The Project Company shall handback all software special tools, special equipment for spare parts for the Tolling System and all Operation and Maintenance Systems assemblies that were purchased to support the O&M Work. The software, spares and assemblies shall be transferred to GOU in a safe, fully functioning and operable condition.",
        "The Project Company shall provide training to GOU staff so that GOU personnel have a complete understanding of the maintenance program, plans, reports and activities related to the operation and maintenance of the Project.",
        "The Project Company shall provide a Handback Report that meets the requirements defined in 5.3.",
        "The Project Company shall ensure that all Handback Deliverables are submitted to the Independent Engineer and GOU prior to Expiry of O&M Term or earlier Termination.",
        "Handback Plan",
        "The Project Company shall prepare a Handback Plan that will be used to determine the condition, performance and residual life of the Project Infrastructure.",
        "The Handback Plan shall be submitted as a condition precedent to Practical Completion and shall be updated at minimum of 5 years.",
        "The Handback Plan shall include the following;",
        "Testing procedures, standards and processes;",
        "The Handback Plan shall include the necessary testing and inspection procedures to assess the condition and performance of all Expressway Assets.",
        "The test and inspection procedures shall indicate any particular reference standards, or other information used to support the testing, inspection and asset evaluation process.",
        "The Plan shall identify the testing, evaluation, and calculation methods that are to be utilized during the condition assessment and the calculation of residual life of each asset and shall utilize applicable industry standards, manufacturer\u2019s life expectancy, equipment mean time between failures, equipment/asset histories to determine the condition, performance and the residual life for each Expressway asset.",
        "The Handback Plan shall include all the pertinent tests, inspections, processes and evaluations required to verify and demonstrate to the Independent Engineer and GOU that all assets function as intended and meet the residual service life requirements as specified in 5.3.",
        "Evaluation of Project Assets following Handback Inspection;",
        "The Handback Plan shall include an evaluation of the Project Assets; and,",
        "The Plan shall include an update of the conditions of the Project infrastructure and any changes in the material assets determined.",
        "Personnel Handover Plan",
        "The Handback Plan shall include a comprehensive list of the personnel and governance structures required to operate and maintain the Expressway at the standard specified in 0 of this agreement.",
        "The Project Company shall also indicate the staff that GOU may opt to take over and the staff that shall be demobilised at the end of the Project Term.",
        "Personnel Training Plan",
        "The Handback Plan shall include a schedule of training of the personnel required to continue with a seamless operation and maintenance of the Project post Handback.",
        "Handback Deliverables",
        "The Handback Plan shall include a schedule of handover of the Handback Deliverables to ensure that all components of the Project are handed over fully.",
        "Handback Tasks and Evaluation Criteria",
        "Expressway Assets",
        "The Project Company will ensure that the Project Infrastructure will be handed back to GOU with all Assets of the Project compliant with the Handback Requirements specified below.",
        "O&M training",
        "GOU shall identify and submit a list of personnel that shall be trained as part of the takeover team to carry out the O&M Activities.",
        "The Project Company shall provide on-job training including job shadowing in accordance with the approved Personnel Training Plan.",
        "The training duration shall be over a period of six (06) months.",
        "These personnel shall not be facilitated by the Project Company; however, the Project Company shall provide all the tools including software, transport and environment for this practical training.",
        "O&M Trial Period",
        "The Project Company shall supervise the personnel to undertake fourteen day 24-hour periods of operations and maintenance for the entire Project within the last two months of expiry of the Project Term.",
        "At the end of the O&M Trial Period, the Project Company will be required to appraise the staff in the new positions on their performance and provide feedback or recommendation to GOU.",
        "During the O&M Trial Period, the Project Company shall be relieved of any O&M performance obligations related to actions of the personnel being trained.",
        "O&M support",
        "The Project Company shall provide personnel for consultation in respect of the O&M Activities for at least one year after Handback.",
        "The Project Company shall provide Human Resource support in transfer of contracts from the Project Company at the end of the O&M Term to ensure continuity of the O&M Activities.",
        "Handback Report",
        "A Handback Report shall be prepared and submitted after every Handback Inspection and shall include, at a minimum:",
        "certification that testing was conducted prior in accordance with the appropriate procedures and standards and otherwise in compliance with this Agreement;",
        "certification of the results of the testing with respect to each test procedures and standards, each of which shall be addressed separately and the basis for the determination presented; this certification of results of the testing shall include a determination of the extent to which the facilities comply with the applicable performance requirements;",
        "all data measured and recorded during the tests including laboratory analyses, instrument calibrations, and measurement;",
        "all calculations used in determining test results;",
        "record of equipment outages, failures, and preventative maintenance performed during the tests;",
        "call centre records for the period of the tests; and",
        "any other data reasonably requested by the Independent Engineer to be included in the report.",
        "The Final Handback Report shall be submitted at least 60 Business Days before the Expiry of the O&M Term and may be used by GOU in preparation of the Handback Notice.",
        "Handback Inspections",
        "Upon submission of the Handback Plan and any update thereafter, the Project Company shall invite the Independent Engineer and GOU to undertake the Handback Inspection.",
        "The Handback Inspection shall be a joint inspection between the Project Company, the Independent Engineer and GOU.",
        "The joint inspections shall be conducted every 5 years and every six months within the last 2 years of the O&M Term.",
        "Following the Handback Inspection, the Project Company shall prepare a Handback Report and update the Handback Plan where required.",
        "The following criteria shall be followed in development of the Handback Plan",
        "The Project Company shall use the Table above as a guideline for the assets, inspections and testing required, however the actual identification of the assets to be evaluated is dependent upon the Project Company\u2019s final design configuration and infrastructure in place at the time of the Handback."
