        "Where a Relevant Event occurs and the Parties agree that the financial consequences of such shall give rise to a revision to the Base Case Financial Model, then such revisions, including revisions to the Base Quarterly Availability Payment and other such parameters as may be necessary on a one-off or recurrent basis, shall be made by Project Company in accordance with this section 8 of this Part A of this schedule 2.  Such revisions shall, on the next Revision Date in accordance with this section 8 of this Part A of this schedule 2, be consolidated as an update to the Base Case Financial Model. Either Party may request Expert Determination under clause 46 of this Agreement where there is a dispute between the Parties as to whether the financial consequences give rise to a revision to the Base Case Financial Model.",
        "Prior to making any changes to the then current Base Case Financial Model (subject to any express provision of this Agreement to the contrary), the Parties shall agree the Revision Date for the change and the basis of the revision to the then current Base Case Financial Model.",
        "Except for revisions due to a Refinancing (in which case the provisions of clause 37 of the Agreement shall apply) in the event that there is a Relevant Event and it is agreed that the level of each Base Quarterly Availability Payment shall be adjusted as a result of the revisions to the then current Base Case Financial Model, each Base Quarterly Availability Payment shall be revised so as to ensure that the Project Company is left in a No Better No Worse position than it was prior to the Revision Date and the occurrence of the Relevant Event which gave rise to the need for the revision.  In no circumstances shall any revision provide compensation to the Project Company for any deviation in performance from that predicted in the latest Base Case Financial Model as agreed between the Parties or determined by Dispute Resolution.",
        "A revision to the then current Base Case Financial Model shall be regarded as leaving the Project Company in a No Better No Worse position if, following the applicable revision, the Key Ratios in the revised Base Case Financial Model are maintained at no lower or no higher levels from the Key Ratios immediately prior to the revision and the Equity IRR after and immediately prior to the revision does not differ by more than five basis points (being zero point zero five).",
