        "to rectify Project Company Events of Default, under clause 41 of the Project Agreement, where such has arisen in relation to the Construction Activities, or a Project Company default under the Construction Contract, both in accordance with its step-in rights under this Agreement,",
        "and the Construction Contractor covenants with GOU that it will permit the exercise of such rights under the Construction Contract in a way which facilitates the effective exercise by GOU of the rights referred to in clause 4.3 and will, on reasonable notice, permit an GOU Delegate to have access to, and take copies of, the records, reports, documents and other papers referred to in clause 4.3(b).",
        "The Construction Contractor hereby grants an irrevocable and royalty free licence (including a right to sub-licence) to GOU to use and reproduce for purposes relating to the Project (including, without limitation, the construction, completion, reconstruction, modification, extension, repair, use, letting, sale and advertisement of the Works, or any part thereof) all plans, drawings, specifications, and calculations (including all Design Documentation and Construction Documentation) relating to the Project, together with all amendments and additions thereto which are now or may at any time in the future be prepared, designed or drawn by the Construction Contractor or its subcontractor, employees or agents and which relate to the Project.",
        "Without prejudice to clause 5, the Construction Contractor shall:",
        "take out all insurances required to be taken out by the Construction Contractor under the Construction Contract (and should it fail to effect or maintain any such insurance policy required under the Construction Contract, or if any insurance policy required under the Construction Contract becomes void or voidable, GOU may (but is not obliged to) effect or maintain that insurance policy at the cost of the Construction Contractor);",
        "otherwise comply with all of its obligations in relation to insurance in the Construction Contract and ensure that it does not do, or omit to do, anything, or does not permit anything to be done, or omitted from being done, whereby any insurance policy required under the Construction Contract may be prejudiced or vitiated; and",
        "ensure that the insurance cover provided by any insurance contract required under the Construction Contract (other than insurance contracts in respect of professional indemnity, employers' liability, workers' compensation or motor vehicle insurance) extends to GOU.",
        "The Project Company and the Construction Guarantor each join in this Agreement to acknowledge and consent to the arrangements set out herein and each hereby agrees to not knowingly do, or omit to do, anything that may prevent any party from enforcing its rights under this Agreement.",
        "Save as expressly stated herein, nothing in this Agreement shall prejudice GOU's general rights at Law.",
        "Contractor's Warranties",
        "The Construction Contractor warrants and undertakes to GOU that it has complied with and will continue to comply with all the terms and conditions of the Construction Contract, whether express or implied, and that it shall complete the Construction Activities in accordance with the Construction Contract.  [Note to Bidders: GOU will conduct due diligence on the draft Construction Contract prior to its execution.  This will ensure, inter alia, that it contains a suitable suite of protections in favour of the Project Company (as employer) including standard warranties as to due incorporation, power to contract, no material litigation, no immunity from suit, no change in financial condition that would prejudice its ability to undertake the Construction Activities etc]",
        "Without prejudice to clause 5.1, the Construction Contractor further warrants and undertakes to GOU that:",
        "it has exercised and will continue to exercise in carrying out the Construction Activities, the reasonable skill and care to be expected from a properly qualified and competent professional construction contractor who is experienced in carrying out works of a similar size, scope, nature, complexity and value to the Construction Activities (and that it has and will continue to supervise all sub-contractors of whatever tier (to such extent as the Construction Contractor has an obligation to supervise, pursuant to the Sub-Contract or at Law) with that same level of skill and care); and",
        "it will not seek to modify or vary any of the obligations for which it is responsible under the Construction Contract other than in accordance with the express terms of the Construction Contract.",
        "The Construction Contractor further warrants that the Construction Contractor's obligations hereunder shall also apply to any amendment to or variation of the Construction Contract.",
        "The Construction Contractor acknowledges and agrees that GOU is deemed to have relied upon and shall continue to rely upon the undertakings and warranties given by the Construction Contractor in this Agreement.",
        "Notwithstanding any other term of this Agreement:",
        "GOU shall not be entitled to bring any claim against the Construction Contractor arising out of or in connection with any breach or non-observance of the terms of the Construction Contract or under this clause 5 unless and until the Project Agreement has been terminated;",
        "the obligations of the Construction Contractor to GOU under this Agreement shall be no greater in duration, extent or quantity than its obligations under the Construction Contract had GOU been named as employer thereunder.  The Construction Contractor shall be entitled, in any action or proceedings by GOU in relation to the Construction Contract or the Construction Activities, to rely on any term in the Construction Contract and to raise the equivalent rights in defence of liability (excluding set-off, counter claim and/or retention) as it would have had against the Project Company under the Construction Contract, provided that the Construction Contractor shall not contend in defence of any claim by GOU under this Agreement that the Project Company has suffered no loss and/or GOU's loss is different in nature and/or extent to that of the Project Company; and",
        "as between the Construction Contractor and the Project Company, the rights of the Construction Contractor under the Construction Contract shall not be varied by this Agreement, save as expressly provided.",
        "No Termination and Lender Step In",
        "The Construction Contractor agrees that it will not exercise any right, howsoever arising (including through termination or proposed termination of the Project Agreement) that it may have to terminate the Construction Contract or to treat the Construction Contract as having been repudiated by the Project Company or to discontinue or suspend the performance of the duties to be performed by the Construction Contractor prior to the expiry of any GOU Step-In Period in accordance with clause 8 of this Agreement.",
        "Compliance by the Construction Contractor with the provisions of clause 6.1 shall not be treated as a waiver by the Construction Contractor of any breach on the part of the Project Company giving rise to the right of termination or damages nor otherwise prevent the Construction Contractor from exercising its rights after the expiration of the GOU Step-In Period, unless the right of termination shall have ceased under the provisions of clause 6.2.",
        "For the avoidance of doubt, and in order for GOU to remain fully advised as to its ability to exercise its rights under this Agreement, the Construction Contractor shall give GOU copies of:",
        "all notices of intention to terminate the Construction Contract it serves on the Project Company given pursuant the terms of the Construction Contract and the Construction Consent Deed, at the same time as they are delivered;",
