        "immediate written notice of the expiry of any Lenders Step-In Period.",
        "[Where the Construction Contractor has given rights in relation to the Construction Contract similar to those contained in clause 8 of this Agreement to the Security Trustee under the Construction Consent Deed then, if more than one of GOU and the Security Trustee serve notice under clause 8.3 or their equivalent, the notice served by the Security Trustee will prevail over any notice served by GOU.  In such case, the GOU Step-In Period shall commence at the end of the Lenders Step-In Period.] [Note to Bidders: See note above about the interface with the Lender's Consent Deed.  If this is not required, then this will be adjusted accordingly]",
        "Notification of Default and/or Right to Terminate",
        "At the same time as the giving of any notice of intention to terminate under the Construction Contract and on the commencement of any GOU Step-In Period, respectively, the Construction Contractor shall notify GOU of:",
        "any of the obligations of the Project Company under the Construction Contract which the Project Company has failed to discharge;",
        "the Construction Contractor's reasonable, good faith estimate of its financial entitlement arising from the Project Company's failure to discharge the Project Company's obligations under the Construction Contract (including any sums claimed pursuant to any principle of Law (including any claim in negligence));",
