        "definitions and INTERPRETATION",
        "Definitions and Interpretations",
        "In this Agreement, terms defined in the Project Agreement and not otherwise defined in this Agreement shall have the meaning given to them in the Project Agreement.",
        "Unless the context otherwise requires, the following terms shall have the following meanings:",
        "\"Guarantee\" means the guarantee given by the O&M Guarantor pursuant to clause 10 in favour of GOU as security for, or in connection with, the performance by the O&M Contractor of its obligations under this Agreement, dated on or about the date of this Agreement;",
        "\"Lenders Step-In Period\" means the period commencing on the date of receipt by the Lenders (or the Security Trustee on their behalf) of notification by the O&M Contractor (under the O&M Consent Deed) that it has become entitled to terminate the O&M Contract in accordance with the terms of the O&M Consent Deed (a copy of which notice shall be sent simultaneously by the O&M Contractor to GOU) and ending on the earlier of:",
        "expiry of the period under the O&M Consent Deed during which the Lenders (or the Security Trustee on their behalf) must decide whether or not to exercise their rights to assume the obligations of the Project Company under the O&M Contract; and",
        "the date, if any, upon which the Lenders (or the Security Trustee on their behalf) advise the O&M Contractor pursuant to the O&M Consent Deed (such notice to be copied immediately by the O&M Contractor to GOU) that they will not assume the obligations of the Project Company under the O&M Contract;",
        "[Note to Bidders: this definition (and associated drafting) assumes that Lenders (or the Security Trustee on their behalf) will also take a subcontractor direct and that, if so, this will take priority over this document.  Should the Lenders (or the Security Trustee on their behalf) choose not to do so, this drafting will be amended accordingly]",
        "\"Nominee\" means that person nominated by GOU that is so authorised, alongside GOU, to give instructions as if it were the Project Company in accordance with clause 8.5;",
        "\"O&M Consent Deed\" means the consent deed dated [] between the O&M Contractor and [] as Security Trustee.",
        "\"Security\" means any unconditional bank undertaking, or other security, provided by the O&M Contractor to the Project Company as security for, or in connection with, the performance by it of its obligations under the O&M Contract, as replaced or reduced from time to time but does not include the Guarantee;",
        "\"Step-In Notice\" has the meaning given in clause 8.3;",
        "\"Surviving Clauses\" has the meaning given in clause 17.1;",
        "\"GOU Delegate\" has the meaning given to such term in clause 3.1;",
        "\"GOU Project Documents\" means []; and",
        "\"GOU Step-In Period\" means the 30 Business Day period (or such longer period as the Parties may agree) commencing on the day GOU receives a written notice from the O&M Contractor of:",
        "the expiry or termination of the Lenders Step-In Period; or",
        "circumstances or events which have arisen giving the O&M Contractor the right (but not the obligation) to terminate the O&M Contract and that such right of termination does not give rise to a step-in right for the Lenders (or the Security Trustee on their behalf) pursuant to the O&M Consent Deed.",
        "Interpretation",
        "In this Agreement (unless the context indicates a contrary intention):",
        "headings (including any heading at the beginning of any clause) are for convenience only and do not affect interpretation;",
        "an obligation or a liability assumed by, or a right conferred on, two or more persons binds or benefits them jointly and severally;",
        "a reference to a \"person\" includes an individual, the estate of an individual, a corporation, an authority, an association or a joint venture (whether incorporated or unincorporated), a partnership and a trust;",
        "a reference to a \"Party\" includes that Party's executors, administrators, successors and permitted assigns, including persons taking by way of novation and, in the case of a trustee, includes a substituted or an additional trustee;",
        "a reference to a \"document\" (including this Agreement) is to that document as varied, novated, ratified or replaced from time to time;",
        "a reference to a \"statute\" includes its delegated legislation and a reference to a statute or delegated legislation or a provision of either includes consolidations, amendments, re-enactments and replacements;",
        "a word importing the singular includes the plural (and vice versa), and a word indicating a gender includes every other gender;",
        "a reference to a \"clause\", \"schedule\", \"exhibit\", \"attachment\" or \"annexure\" is a reference to a clause, schedule, exhibit, attachment or annexure to or of this Agreement, and a reference to this Agreement includes all schedules, exhibits, attachments and annexures to it;",
        "if a word or phrase is given a defined meaning, any other part of speech or grammatical form of that word or phrase has a corresponding meaning;",
        "\"includes\" (and any other form of that word) is not a word of limitation;",
        "where a right or remedy is conferred on GOU under this Agreement, that right or remedy is in addition to, and not in substitution of, any other right or remedy conferred on GOU under this Agreement or otherwise according to Law;",
        "where an obligation or liability is imposed on the Project Company, the O&M Contractor or the O&M Guarantor under this Agreement, that obligation or liability is not to be limited or affected by an obligation or liability imposed in another provision of this Agreement unless expressly stated;",
        "references to a \"notice\", \"notification\", \"record\", \"report\", \"consent\", \"agreement\", \"disclosure\" or \"approval\" or any variation of those words are references to a notice, notification, record, report, consent, agreement, disclosure, approval or any variation of those words, in writing;",
        "if more than one requirement imposed on the Project Company, whether under a Project Document or otherwise, applies in respect of any part of the Project, then all requirements must be satisfied.  If there are requirements which are mutually exclusive, then the requirement which delivers the greatest level of service, or is of the highest standard, shall apply;",
